The President held a briefing with his team to discuss the ongoing response and recovery efforts in the affected region. They also discussed the severe weather forecasted for the coming days and the efforts by FEMA to provide necessary resources to potentially impacted communities. The President emphasized the need to continue supporting state and local partners, especially in fuel challenges and power restoration. They also discussed the long-term housing solutions for survivors whose homes have been damaged, with FEMA administering a program to temporarily provide hotel and motel rooms. Additional assistance was approved for debris removal efforts in Connecticut, New Jersey, and New York. Secretary Napolitano is visiting Nassau County, NY, to assess the response and recovery efforts.